      "content": "I hear you on the regulatory risks, but the board is still leaning towards the overhaul because \"unsustainable\" is a huge red flag for investors. They're worried that trying to be \"equitable\" is just a way of ignoring the hard reality of risk in these specific areas. They're basically saying that if we lose the predictive power that comes with these current patterns, the whole portfolio collapses. If we do this reset, you'll lose the specific weightings that currently prevent us from going bankrupt due to defaults. How can you justify the \"equitable\" path if it means we might not survive the transition period?",
